The milk of midnight the stars and you.\
\
The milk of abuse\
It\'92s not love you feel, is terror\
\
And God said, \'93never let a sorceress live.\'94\
\
The social clubs staged the raid\
to steal the bulls that night.\
I watched from the Ees,\
the face of the policeman passing\
between pillars of utter darkness.\
I saw the dog just before the rain.\
\
I lost you, torn apart in a riot, \
by pale hands.\
\'93Rangoon,\'94 the policeman called out\
to the German shepherd,\
\'93end of strife,\'94 \'93big dog.\'94\
\
Withdrawn from the night,\
from every branch,\
pulled from the rooftops,\
battering the trees in the street-\
one last breath.\
\
The warm air was thick,\
naked in the weather.\
And all at once,\
a blanket of rain\
seals the whole town in that moment.\
\
Found there, on the right bank,\
was the body.\
\
From the corner of your mouth,\
true love sleeps like a bloodhound\
jowls of longing,\
black lips suede,\
pony fur.\
Like seeing stars,\
smacks of desperation.\
\
Buttercup,\
my olive heart sleeps.\
A light shines through-\
steam peach peach.\
 \
Inspired in me,\
the thing that tore us apart-\
\
the ouroboros.\
If it had been,\
it would have bit me.\
\
The milk of bred in captivity.\
\
Your silent breath,\
your invisible skin.\
You touch yourself alone,\
become hot steam.\
\
A lamplight from a window pane,\
lost like a ring in the evenin\'92.\
\
Estranged on the Mersey,\
sleepwalking.\
Bones exposed\
eggshells and pebbles.\
The skeleton, mind made up,\
along the narrow way home.\
I loved you on the mountaintop,\
and I walked the ocean alone.\
\
\'93I said you could be there, all alone with me,\'94\
walking through the camps.\
You said, \'93God left us\
never existed.\'94\
\
The milk of spilt milk,\
\
put upon the back of that man\
wishing he was an exotic animal,\
a rock pool,\
or Chinese food.\
\
Good night has killed himself,\
like thank you,\
and sorry.\
\
Oumuamua,\
the milk of pepper.\
\
And God said,\
\'93the thief will return,\
back fivefold,\
for each bull he stole.\'94\
