\
Bastard balm and melancholy.\
Ghost orchids on the news.\
Poplar seeds fill the air,\
and we will never see each other again.\
\
I yield.\
\
\'93And for the bull who saved the life of the tortoise\'85\'94 God said.\
\
You steal the night,\
you hide it from the people.\
It whispers to you from your wallet\
\'93guilty,\'92\'92 it says, \'93murderer.\'92\'92\
The whole world grieves for the night.\
\
The night takes you in his\
empty hands.\
\
He makes you cum-\
like hot steam,\
in the lamplight,\
in the window,\
lost like a jewel\
from the sky.\
