White noise of sycamore,\
of birch.\
Light strange through ash-\
like snow.\
\
\'93Guilty.\'92\'92\
\
I hate your silver linings,\
but I see it all written in the stars,\
written in stress.\
\
\'93Poison.\'94\
\
It decorates the doors to the other side,\
carved into stone,\
written on the threshold\
where I see it all happening.\
\
\'93Thief.\'92\'92\
\
The wind blows voices\
between the ticks of the clock.\
The cat cries \'93Ah la la.\'94\
\
For you, I imagine nights are filled\
with a deep sense of belonging.\
\
If I pinched myself, would I be dreaming?\
If I cut myself, would I bleed?\
\
Just a little by little,\
the street turned to ash in my ears.\
And over coffee, I ignored everything I ever felt,\
submitting myself.\
\
The milk was fat and thick,\
and the sugar stole away any feeling.\
I left tracks in the foam-\
longing to be the steam that escaped the morning\
with a howl.\
\
Whipped into nothing.\
