\cf0 The new world was black. Because now there is nothing but blackness.\
And the billowing sound of my own voice echoing in the dark.\
\
In the echoes, I looked into the blackness with no eyes.\
Until I saw the mirror.\
The words still in the air now, crashing the way the sea changes.\
The mirror with no one in it went on forever and ever.\
But as I pointed, the tracers flashed before me\'97\
Aurora, red-hot in the wind.\
The wind that says the new world is black.\
The mirror filled with snow, a mirage. And the treeless heights gave no clues.\
The tundra of little fires at my feet hid from my gaze.\
\
My voice, my breath.\
The wind asks on and on, \'93What\'92s the matter with you, Ash?\'94\
\
The one million needles I spilled in the dark. Pinpricks of a world.\
No longer at rest, I shushed my mind, mumbling.\
The shadows escaped the night, the moon, the mirror, and the stars.\
And the charcoal in the wash said:\
\
\'93I am the shadows.\'94\
\
